Text.Value: But - I won't make it that long on my own.
Of course, girl. You can help me determine who it is doing all the snoring.

EditorData.NodeContext: Warmth, suppressing pity - a young girl has just asked to stay at our camp, hinting that her mother is probably dead. Offering up a joke / activity to make her feel at ease.

Text.Value: Ugh. Fine. Get your stuff and come on in.
No kids allowed. Come back in ten years.
Of course you can stay, Yenna. Pick a spot and settle in.
But erm. But - all right. I'll go. But you'll see - you should've said yes. You'll wish you said yes.

EditorData.NodeContext: Might sound a little bit like a threat, but really she's just going to come back and cook for the player.

Text.Value: I met you before. And erm. My mum hasn't come back yet. She might come later... I don't think she's coming.
You were really nice to me before. And erm. My mum hasn't come back yet. She might come later... I don't think she's coming.
I brought my own paring knife; now I just need some ingredients and... I'm gonna make something really good, I promise!
Thankyouthankyou! I won't get in the way. I promise!
I would rather share my camp with goblins again.
Could I maybe stay here?
You don't?
Yes! We can play one-a-cup!
Could we maybe stay here?
Ugh. Isn't there a human cr√®che she can join?
YES! You've got a fire and everything. I can cook really good! Whatever you want! Thankyouthankyou.
Erm. Hi. It's me. Yenna. You remember me, right?
It isn't much of a home, but what's ours is yours.
I don't have any stuff. But I can cook!
What harm? She's little - won't take up much space, or make much of a dent in our provisions.
I already told you no - I meant it.
If the child's desperate enough to seek safety in our company, who are we to turn her away?
Absolutely not. We've hit our quota for mangy strays.
Of course! Boo could use an extra friend to play 'chase the Boo', seeing as none here are quick enough.
Only a truly callous heart could refuse. Besides, our little abode could use a child's laughter.
Erm. Hi. It's me. Yenna. You remember me, right?
Sorry, kid. I don't think so.

Synopsis: Yenna approaches the camp to ask if they can stay. The player has met Yenna once before she comes to camp.
